class Solution:
    def isLongPressedName(self, name: str, typed: str) -> bool:
        i, j = 0, 0

        while j < len(typed):
            if i < len(name) and name[i] == typed[j]:
                i += 1
            elif j == 0 or typed[j] != typed[j - 1]:
                return False
            j += 1

        return i == len(name)
```

This solution uses two pointers to traverse the `name` and `typed` strings. It checks if each character in `name` matches the corresponding character in `typed`, allowing for long-pressed characters in `typed`. If a character in `typed` does not match the current character in `name` and is not a repetition of the previous character in `typed`, it returns `False`. Finally, it checks if all characters in `name` have been matched.
